<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-23T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="757" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">361.1121 K 55/129: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-23T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 23,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>71. Repeat your No. 444, June 21, to Embassy London and Legation
                            Christiania.</p>
                        <p>Is it possible, in your opinion, that effective pressure for release of
                            Americans can be exercised by Baltic States in case they were asked to
                            do so by this Government?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>